<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-11T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1986: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-11T22:00:00-04:00">February
                                    11, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Your 134, February 5. If occasion arises, you may advise your British
                            and Russian colleagues that Department, on basis of its present
                            information, does not regard Seyid Zia-ed-Din Tabatabai as a suitable
                            person to head Iranian Government. Our opinion is based upon both his
                            record and the fact that he has been away from Iran for past 20 years.
                            Accordingly, we would not be disposed to encourage any movement for his
                            return to power.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>